name: Mineola Wisener Field Airport
about: Mineola Wisener Field Airport, established in 1917 and operated by the same family since 1926, is the oldest privately owned public use airport in Texas. Our flying school, Ivy Aviation Services, offers comprehensive flight training programs led by experienced instructor Jim Ivy. With a rich history spanning over 106 years, our airport provides a unique and supportive environment for aspiring pilots. Our facilities include two runways and a range of airport services, ensuring a thorough and safe learning experience. Join us to embark on your aviation journey at a piece of American aviation history.
